%N A394738 Numbers k such that sigma(k) = psi(k) + tau(k) + Omega(k)^3.
%C A394738 a(8) > 10^10, if it exists. - _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 31 2026
%e A394738 184 is a term since sigma(184) = 360 = 288 + 8 + 4^3 = psi(184) + tau(184) + Omega(184)^3.
%o A394738 (PARI) isok(k) = {my(f = factor(k)); sigma(f) == prod(i=1, #f~, (f[i, 1]+1) * f[i, 1]^(f[i, 2]-1)) + numdiv(f) + bigomega(f)^3; } \\ _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 30 2026
